Package org.sopra.api.model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CapacityEdge<V>
    The capacity edge extends the Edge-Interface for ability of changing the flow.
    Controllable
    Controllable is an interface that allows to gain information about controllable graph elements.
    Edge<V>
    The edge of a graph.
    EnergyNode
    Nodes in a scenario graph.
    Graph<N,​E extends Edge<N>>
    This interface represents a directed capacitive graph.
    PlantLocation
    Plant location is an interface for a data container that holds both an energy node and the playfield element with the same coordinates.
    Playfield
    The playfield represents the land where the scenario is located.
    PlayfieldElement
    One tile of the playfield.
    PowerLine
    The interface for the actual power lines in the scenario.
    TransformerStation
    Transformer stations are "empty" nodes.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Multiplier
    This factor is used for several cost calculations.
    PlayfieldElement.ElementType
    An enumeration to simplify the selection of the type of a play field element: beach river grassland sea mountain
    PowerLineType
    An enumeration to simplify the selection of the type of a power line: low voltage medium voltage high voltage
